    {
      "id": "VW230rZSG94onj7zf7FLY",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3328.866339961274,
      "y": -2930.5919127821226,
      "width": 2462.7454743372905,
      "height": 1009.0619325140609,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a1",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 121875119,
      "version": 4096,
      "versionNonce": 2144457161,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1783746680146,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\nC:  how the workflow should get trigger ? via webhooks, scheduler or manual. \nI: lets start with manual but should be extensible. \n\nC: what kind of nodes do we need to support ? Triggers, Integration Actions, General API Node,\n Conditional Nodes, Agent Node, Function Node, Scheduler, Response, Router ?   \nI: At a minimum we will support General API Node, Conditional Node, Function Node, Integration Action Node & Response Node\n\nC: okay so we have nodes and edges, we must define how each nodes get connected to other nodes. \ndirected, can their be cycle, can we have multiple branches from same node each branch runs concurrently, which all nodes can connect one, two and more than two node.\nI: we will have directed graph (from = to), and cycle is disallowed (DAG). \n\n    Response Node = 1 Incoming, 0 Outgoing\n    Start Node = 0 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n    Conditional Node = 1 Incoming, 2 Outgoing\n    Function Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n    General Api Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing, \n    Integration Action Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n\nC: this looks good, are we targeting to handle errors ? what if conditional node fails (incoming corrupted data), function node fails (execution failed for unknown reason), in integration action and api node, what if response\nwith status other than 2** (token expired, request time outs). \nI: we must handle this error gracefully.\n\nC: should we support atomic workflow execution, whole workflow rollback if one of the node fails and mark it as \"FAILED\" or we need to have an ability to start workflow from where it failed. \nI: for simplicity lets just have ability to start workflow from where it failed, if time persist we will talk about atomic workflow exection\n\nC: do we need to store node level traces and workflow level logs for each workflow ? \nI: lets store the workflow level logs and if time persist we will add node level traces. \n\nC: How many times workflows are run per day and how many combined user workflows we have ? \nI: 1M times/day , 100K combined workflows\n\nC: Do we need to assume we have Integrations and their Credentials already build by other team or we need to build it ? \nI: for simplicity just assume we already have Integration Infrastruture and Auth in Place. We will use Composio.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 22.423598500312465,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nC:  how the workflow should get trigger ? via webhooks, scheduler or manual. \nI: lets start with manual but should be extensible. \n\nC: what kind of nodes do we need to support ? Triggers, Integration Actions, General API Node,\n Conditional Nodes, Agent Node, Function Node, Scheduler, Response, Router ?   \nI: At a minimum we will support General API Node, Conditional Node, Function Node, Integration Action Node & Response Node\n\nC: okay so we have nodes and edges, we must define how each nodes get connected to other nodes. \ndirected, can their be cycle, can we have multiple branches from same node each branch runs concurrently, which all nodes can connect one, two and more than two node.\nI: we will have directed graph (from = to), and cycle is disallowed (DAG). \n\n    Response Node = 1 Incoming, 0 Outgoing\n    Start Node = 0 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n    Conditional Node = 1 Incoming, 2 Outgoing\n    Function Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n    General Api Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing, \n    Integration Action Node = 1 Incoming, 1 Outgoing\n\nC: this looks good, are we targeting to handle errors ? what if conditional node fails (incoming corrupted data), function node fails (execution failed for unknown reason), in integration action and api node, what if response with status other than 2** (token expired, request time outs). \nI: we must handle this error gracefully.\n\nC: should we support atomic workflow execution, whole workflow rollback if one of the node fails and mark it as \"FAILED\" or we need to have an ability to start workflow from where it failed. \nI: for simplicity lets just have ability to start workflow from where it failed, if time persist we will talk about atomic workflow exection\n\nC: do we need to store node level traces and workflow level logs for each workflow ? \nI: lets store the workflow level logs and if time persist we will add node level traces. \n\nC: How many times workflows are run per day and how many combined user workflows we have ? \nI: 1M times/day , 100K combined workflows\n\nC: Do we need to assume we have Integrations and their Credentials already build by other team or we need to build it ? \nI: for simplicity just assume we already have Integration Infrastruture and Auth in Place. We will use Composio.\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
